title: Claude Monet Water Lilies Zip Case
description:
Zip Case developed from Claude Monet’s Water Lilies, 1906, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection. 

Claude Monet (French, 1840-1926) is one of the greatest and most endearingly popular artists of all time. Monet's work went through many thematic and stylistic phases during his long career; always his goal was to capture the impression on the viewer's eye and record the visual sensation of light and color that guided his brush. 

Case has two zipped sections and a removable wrist-loop that hooks to the case. 

  • Dimensions: 8 x 6 x 1 in.
  • Material: 100% Neoprene.
  • Hand wash, hang dry.
